# Trivy suppression list for the published image scan.
#
# One CVE ID per line. Lines starting with '#' are comments.
# Pin every suppression to a reason and (ideally) an expiry — stale entries
# rot quickly. Use this only when:
#   1. Upstream has not yet released a fix, AND
#   2. The vuln is not exploitable in our usage (e.g. unreachable code path), OR
#      we accept the risk and have a tracking issue.
#
# Format:
#   CVE-XXXX-NNNN  # short reason; tracker link; expiry YYYY-MM-DD
#
# Example (not active):
#   CVE-2024-12345  # false positive: affected fn not reachable; tracking #42
